						               													<description>Sulphur can be used to fight enjoyable one-off SF games using easy to organise forces of varying points cost. Alternately, players can opt for a longer series of joined-up battles against an opponent where success or failure will not be determined by one encounter but by a series of battles.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This is where the Sulphur Campaign rules come in. Here players can fight a series of interlinked battles that require strategic as well as tactical thinking. Problems of supply, resources and territory will have to be dealt with as well as the more usual concerns - such as smashing-up your enemy! In a campaign game, players must build up as many resources as possible, to increase the size and strength of their faction. As the opposing group will be trying to do the same thing, players will have to deploy their forces in the most effective way to counter this threat.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Sulphur Campaign has added a lot more background detail to the Sulphur World. A lively, unusual and often grim post-apocalyptic world that covers such elements as -&amp;#10;Trading, Scavenging, Spoils of War, Repairs, Ammo and Food supply, Tithes and Protection Money (from bigger meaner factions), the influence of the Church (only if you have paid your tithe), Shaman, Random Events, the Calendar (seasons of the Sulphur year) and the Weather (its usually not very nice!).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
